title: For Sale/Trade:  Mosin Nagant M91/59 "The KGB Mosin"
postcontent: Absolutely beautiful Mosin Nagant M91/59 Carbine. This is not a M38 but a rare unique rifle surrounded in controversy. Many historians say these rifles were modified to the current configuration in Bulgaria to help fight off a US invasion during the height of the cold war. These rifles are cut down M91/30's unlike their M38/M44 carbine cousins. They have a heavier barrel than the other carbines and lend to better accuracy. This rifle is a true all numbers matching example with no electro penciled parts including the stock. The original rifle was produced in 1943 at the Izhevsk factory. The fit & finish is outstanding and the rifle is in excellent condition. These are a must have for any Mosin collector & currently this is the only 91/59 listed on Armslist in the entire country. Will come with sling & ammo pouches513-805-9517
